issue.title: Maximum call stack size exceeded [since version 2.15.4]
issue.body:
First of all thanks a lot for your amazing obfuscator tool ;) 

## Current Behavior
I got an error when I'm load my code (with eval(myObfuscatedCode)) : **Maximum call stack size exceeded**

## Your Environment
I was able to conclude that the error occurs from the **version 2.15.4** of the javascript-obfuscator lib (and still here on 4.1.0)

I'm obfuscating an app builded with _parcel-bundler_ 

My Preset :
```
{
	compact: true,
	controlFlowFlattening: false,
	controlFlowFlatteningThreshold: 0.5,
	deadCodeInjection: false,
	debugProtection: true,
	debugProtectionInterval: 4000,
	disableConsoleOutput: true, 
	identifierNamesGenerator:
		IdentifierNamesGenerator.MangledIdentifierNamesGenerator,
	log: false,
	renameGlobals: false, 
	rotateStringArray: true,
	selfDefending: true,
	stringArray: true,
	stringArrayEncoding: [StringArrayEncoding.Rc4],
	stringArrayThreshold: 0.5,
	transformObjectKeys: false, 
	unicodeEscapeSequence: false
}
```
I found 4 differents ways to fix the bug:

     - Remove Rc4 of stringArrayEncoding
     - disable selfDefending
     - disable debugProtection
     - slightly change my souce parcel builded code by removing the line `var global = arguments[3] ` or just put my code in a minimizer before obfuscating it

# Stack traces
Uncaught (in promise) RangeError: Maximum call stack size exceeded
    at new RegExp (<anonymous>)
    at n.Mhfust (eval at <anonymous> (direct.html:27:9), <anonymous>:1:788008)
    at l (eval at <anonymous> (direct.html:27:9), <anonymous>:1:788486)
    at l (eval at <anonymous> (direct.html:27:9), <anonymous>:1:788554)
    at Function.eval (eval at <anonymous> (direct.html:27:9), <anonymous>:1:7787)
    at n.Mhfust (eval at <anonymous> (direct.html:27:9), <anonymous>:1:788088)
    at l (eval at <anonymous> (direct.html:27:9), <anonymous>:1:788486)
    at l (eval at <anonymous> (direct.html:27:9), <anonymous>:1:788554)
    at Function.eval (eval at <anonymous> (direct.html:27:9), <anonymous>:1:7787)
    at n.Mhfust (eval at <anonymous> (direct.html:27:9), <anonymous>:1:788088)

Uncaught RangeError: Maximum call stack size exceeded
    at l (<anonymous>:5:786723)
    at l (<anonymous>:5:788481)
    at Function.<anonymous> (<anonymous>:5:7792)
    at n.yKWPlE (<anonymous>:5:788015)
    at l (<anonymous>:5:788413)
    at l (<anonymous>:5:788481)
    at Function.<anonymous> (<anonymous>:5:7792)
    at n.yKWPlE (<anonymous>:5:788015)
    at l (<anonymous>:5:788413)
    at l (<anonymous>:5:788481)

I would like to know what's happening, and where that bug is comming from, and fix it without changing my preset.

comment.body: Just found another way to fix the bug : set the seed at 1000 (maybe some other random values too), but I need to have différents codes at each obfuscations, so not a solution for me
